This product includes software developed as an open-source project.

ExeClaw uses the following third-party technologies:

- Firecracker (Apache 2.0) — https://github.com/firecracker-microvm/firecracker
  Lightweight virtual machine monitor for serverless computing.

- nullclaw — AI coding agent that runs inside the Firecracker VMs.

- marked (MIT) — https://github.com/markedjs/marked
  Markdown parser and compiler.

- DOMPurify (Apache 2.0/MIT) — https://github.com/cure53/DOMPurify
  XSS sanitizer for HTML.

- ansi_up (MIT) — https://github.com/drudru/ansi_up
  ANSI escape code to HTML converter.

Inspired by:
- Shelley (https://github.com/boldsoftware/shelley) — exe.dev's coding agent,
  whose agent-working indicator pattern and diff rendering approach influenced
  ExeClaw's UI design.
- exe.dev (https://exe.dev) — the VM platform that ExeClaw is designed to run on.
